reviews.review_text:
Best of what's available.... This is a really good show, with the overwhelming audience electricity and excitement of the Atlanta shows preceding it - but all four recordings here are sub-par.  This is, IMHO, the best because of the Nakamichi mics that pick up the full range of sound and captures the vocal harmonies, drums, and the entire band without the loud, tinny, twangyness of two or the other recordings and the muddiness of the other.
On this recording, just jack up the volume a couple extra notches and enjoy!  For those who listen on other than big ole Bose (front channels) and JBL (rear channels) studio monitor speakers, only reprocessing will get you a satisfactory mix, but there is gracious plenty to work with on this recording to achieve that goal.
To point folks in the right direction, I am giving this recording a generous 5 - it's that much better than the others in present sound and potential for better with a mix-down (er, mix-UP actually...).
Stay in Touch...
